<br>
Your primary spec can go to 200,  the other four are locked at 50.<br>
<br>
These values give a certain unknown (unless ive missed someone posting data) % chance of a successful specilization check. Which reduces fizzles and mana used when succesful.<br>
<br>
SCM just adds a % to those rolls.<br>
<br>
SCM1 gives an additional 5%<br>
SCM2 gives an additional 15%<br>
SCM3 gives an additional 30%<br>
<br>
So having SCM3 would add 30% more chance to make a succesfull specilization check on your &quot;primary&quot; specilization that is at 200, or any of the lower ones at a skill level of 50.<br>
<br>
