<br>
Strip off all or most of your gear, especially INT, mana, FT, and focus effects.  From a full mana bar, count how many times you can cast a high mana spell from your specialization.<br>
<br>
Barring fizzles, you will find that you can always cast that spell exactly the same number of times before you do not have enough mana to cast one more.<br>
<br>
If specialization were random, then sometimes you would <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;make&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> your roll, sometimes not, and the amount of mana expended would vary.  Thus, the number of casts on your mana bar would vary.<br>
<br>
But it does not.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Spell Casting Mastery</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is the best caster archetype AA, bar none.  However, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Spell Casting Fury</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> does impress groups, and may help your reputation, and hence groupability.<br>
